        public static double sqrt​(double n,
                          double tolerance)
        Finds the square root of a given number by constantly bringing a guess of one closer and closer to the actual square root by changing the guess to the average of the guess and the quotient of the original number and that guess, within a specified range of error.
        Parameters:
        n - The number to be square-rooted
        tolerance - The percent error allowed for the calculation
        Returns:
        The square root of the input
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the number entered is negative, and thus can't be used
